a critical assessment of the obama administration's latin america policy center for latin american studies jump to navigation stanford university center for latin american studies search this site home events a critical assessment of the obama administration's latin america policy a critical assessment of the obama administration's latin america policy tuesday january 17 2012 12 15pm 1 05pm o keefe will offer a critical analysis of the obama administration's policies for latin america and the caribbean to date focusing in particular on the the energy and climate partnership of the americas ecpa which is the only initiative new to the obama white house that encompasses the entire western hemisphere in his remarks o keefe will refer to research included in a chapter he wrote for the recently published inter american cooperation at a crossroads thomas andrew o keefe is interim chair of the western hemisphere area studies program at the us state department's foreign service institute and is also the president of mercosur consulting group ltd http www mercosurconsulting net a legal and economic consulting firm that assists companies with their strategic business planning for south america as well as advises latin american firms exporting to the united states the firm was founded in new york in 1993 and moved to washington dc in 1996 mr o keefe is a dual national of the united states and chile he is bilingual in english and spanish and fluent in french and portuguese he did his undergraduate work at columbia university and received his jd from the villanova university school of law mr o keefe is the author of numerous articles on latin american economic integration and globalization and has lectured extensively on the topic both in the united states and abroad he is the author of latin american trade agreements and latin american and caribbean trade agreements keys to a prosperous community of the americas he currently teaches courses at stanford on political economy of the southern cone and economic integration of the americas through the department of international relations and energy cooperation in the western hemisphere through earth systems thomas andrew o keefe lecturer in international relations stanford university bolivar house 582 alvarado row attachment size o keefe pdf 195.09 kb last updated january 25 2012 10 58am calendar main menu about degree programs visiting faculty & scholar programs grants & fellowships people events newsletter giving to clas secondary menu stanford home ica clasp login contact stanford university center for latin american studies bolivar house 582 alvarado row stanford ca 94305 usa phone 650.723 4444 fax 650.723 9822 stanford university terms of use copyright complaints
